Sprint C10 — op-codegen-projection widen: validates → required field
========================================================================
Started/closed: 2026-06-02 (same session)
Base: nexgen=80f938a (post-C8+C9 merge of PRs #12+#13)
Workbench: nexgen workspace directly

Outcome: GREEN. 29/29 tests pass across the codegen family.
         First vocabulary widening of the projection: consumes
         `(_validate, reads_field, …)` triples from ruff_spo_triplet's
         synthetic validator and translates them into SurrealQL field
         requiredness (`TYPE any` vs `TYPE option<any>`).

What landed:
  crates/op-codegen-projection/src/lib.rs
    - DefineField gains pub `required: bool` field
    - Two new const exports: PRED_READS_FIELD, VALIDATE_FN_SUFFIX
    - project(): third pass detecting `(ns:T._validate, reads_field,
      ns:T.col)` → marks `col` on `T` as required (BTreeSet<(table, col)>
      lookup; deterministic; same-table only by construction)
    - surreal_text(): emits `TYPE any` for required, `TYPE option<any>`
      for optional; doc updated to spell out the future-widening seam
    - 5 new tests appended to the projection's #[cfg(test)] mod
  crates/op-codegen-pipeline/src/lib.rs
    - 1 new test: pipeline_validate_function_marks_field_as_required
      drives a synthetic ruff_spo_triplet::Function{name:"_validate", …}
      through expand → bridge → project → emit and asserts:
        * subject.required == true
        * status.required == false
        * text contains "DEFINE FIELD subject ON TABLE WorkPackage TYPE any;"
        * text contains "DEFINE FIELD status ON TABLE WorkPackage TYPE option<any>;"
        * roundtrip_eq still passes

What did NOT land (intentionally deferred):
  - schema.rb column typing (string/integer/etc.) — needs ruff to emit
    type triples first; today schema.rb columns are bare names
  - FK record links (TYPE record<foo>) — needs an explicit predicate
    for foreign-key relationships in the ruff vocabulary
  - ASSERT clauses — beyond simple presence, validation is not
    currently expanded into triples
  - PERMISSIONS — Rails has no analog; deferred indefinitely
  - Indexes — needs an explicit predicate

